through the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GUI app or the ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" CLI — both backed by the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a future release.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the CLI"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"],"type":"codeListing"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook clone"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instant copies."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the GUI"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open Spooktacular."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"+"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button or press "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Cmd+N"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into a new VM bundle.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Managing-VMs","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Managing VMs"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"type":"codeListing"},{"style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CapacityCheck"},{"type":"text","text":" for details."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"ssh","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"progress. See ","type":"text"},{"code":"ProvisioningMode","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for provisioning strategies and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"doc:Provisioning","type":"text"},{"text":" for detailed guidance.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"EC2 Mac Setup"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"release. See "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"},{"type":"text","text":" for the planned architecture."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/MLWorkloads","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Guides"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"]}],"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular"},"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GitHubActionsGuide":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run self-hosted macOS GitHub Actions runners in Spooktacular VMs with ephemeral isolation and automatic scaling."}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/githubactionsguide","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Configuring GitHub Actions Runners"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS